description.plain:
Travis Scott and Quavo are hip-hop artists who collaborate as the supergroup, HUNCHO JACK. The name conjoins two aliases of Quavo and Travis, “Quavo Huncho” and “Cactus Jack”, respectively.

On December 22nd, 2017, they dropped their first collaborative project, titled Huncho Jack, Jack Huncho.

Quavo and Travis had worked together on many songs before their album, including “Oh My Dis Side,” “Quintana (Remix)” “Pick Up the Phone,” and “Kelly Price.” With their strong chemistry over a host of trap-flavored beats, the duo consistently creates bangers.

songs.title: Dubai Shit

description.plain:
After a brief introduction from Swedish artist Yung Lean, Migos' Offset joins Quavo and Travis Scott on “Dubai Shit”. The track revolves around Dubai, an ultramodern city in the United Arab Emirates, and the trio’s lavish lifestyle compared to it.

Following a few years of rumors and leaks, the track represents Travis and Lean’s first collaboration since 2014’s Ghosttown. Dubai Shit also features production from Yung Gud, one of Lean’s best friends and fellow member of the Sadboys collective, consisting of Lean, Yung Sherman and Gud.

It is also notable that Quavo mentions an event that happened in Dubai, being DJ Esco’s arrest for marijuana possession.

songs.title: Modern Slavery

description.plain: “Modern Slavery” starts off the highly anticipated collaboration album between Travis Scott and Quavo. The duo draws parallels between slavery that occurred in America hundreds of years ago, and the notion that they are enslaved to their life’s luxuries such as nice cars, fine jewelry, and tripping on drugs.

songs.title: Black & Chinese

description.plain:
On the second track of Huncho Jack, Jack Huncho, Quavo and Travis Scott talk about drugs and their lavish lifestyles. The title of the track serves as a homage to the types of women that are their preferences.

The song was produced by 808 Mafia member Southside, who worked with both artists on multiple occasions.
